Homework 1¶

Jan Dziuba

Dataset¶

I chose the MagicTelescope dataset.
Dataset is used for classification of high energy gamma particles in a ground-based atmospheric Cherenkov gamma telescope using the imaging technique.
For more detailed description check
https://www.openml.org/search?type=data&sort=runs&id=1120&status=active

Dataset contains 10 features and 19020 samples.
Classes are imbalanced with 1.8438995215311005 ratio.

The features are not normally distributed, so they will require normalization.

The fConc and fConc1 features are heavily correlated.
We could consider removing one of them.

Evaluation¶

I use random 20% of the data for evaluation.
I compare 4 models.
LogisticRegression, RandomForest, xgboost and tabpfn.
For RandomForest and xgboost I use RandomizedSearch and cross validation to find the best hyperparameters.

For evaluation the best metric will be f1 score since it works better than AUC on imbalanced datasets.

In [15]:
def evaluate_model(model, X_test, Y_test):
    pred = model.predict(X_test)
    pred_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

    accuracy = accuracy_score(Y_test, pred)
    precision = precision_score(Y_test, pred)
    recall = recall_score(Y_test, pred)
    auc = roc_auc_score(Y_test, pred_proba)
    f1 = f1_score(Y_test, pred)

    print('Accuracy: {}'.format(accuracy))
    print('Precision: {}'.format(precision))
    print('Recall: {}'.format(recall))
    print('AUC: {}'.format(auc))
    print('F1: {}'.format(f1))
